LEADERSHIP
Blackline’s executive team drives our business forward with customers at the core of everything we do. With deep product development and manufacturing knowledge, extensive investment into research and development and a highly experienced management team, Blackline is ready to help you address your work-alone safety monitoring requirements.







Barry Moore
Vice President, Product Development





Barry Moore
Vice President, Product Development





Barry Moore currently holds an executive position as Vice President of Product Development. He has also served as Vice President of Product Development for BW Technologies, Ltd., formerly listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange prior to its acquisition. Mr. Moore holds a diploma in Industrial Design from Fanshawe College in London Ontario.





Sean Stinson
VP Sales and Product Management





Sean Stinson
VP Sales and Product Management





Prior to taking a position with Blackline, Mr. Stinson occupied the roles of Project Manager and then Systems and Software Engineering at BW Technologies. He later assumed the role of Product Marketing Manager at Honeywell Analytics. Mr. Stinson is a graduate of the University of Calgary’s Electrical Engineering Program.





Kevin Meyers
Chief Operating Officer





Kevin Meyers
Chief Operating Officer





Kevin Meyers currently holds the position of Chief Operating Officer with Blackline GPS, after joining the company from his position of VP of Operations at Imaging Dynamics Corporation (“IDC”), a publicly listed company on the Toronto Venture Exchange. Prior to IDC, Kevin worked as the VP of Operations for BW Technologies, Ltd for 8 years. BW Technologies was formerly listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange before its acquisition by First Technology (2004) and finally Honeywell (2006). Kevin was instrumental in bringing new technologies in house to reduce cost and improve margins on several of their product lines.





Shane Grennan
Chief Financial Officer





Shane Grennan
Chief Financial Officer





Shane Grennan is a Chartered Professional Accountant with a broad range of experience in accounting, finance and audit, spanning several industries in Canada and Ireland. Prior to joining Blackline, Mr. Grennan worked as the Controller of a Mitsubishi Corporation subsidiary in  the natural gas industry and with PricewaterhouseCoopers as a Senior Manager in their audit and assurance group. He offers a broad range of experience that includes financial reporting in accordance with I.F.R.S., U.S. GAAP and Canadian standards, audit procedures, establishing and testing an internal control framework and ERP system implementation.





Cody Slater
Chief Executive Officer & Chair





Cody Slater
Chief Executive Officer & Chair





Cody Slater founded BW Technologies in 1986, a global manufacturer of industrial and commercial gas detection devices with a product line of more than 30 unique instruments. From the Calgary head office, he grew the company’s operations to include offices throughout the world. His impact on one of the country’s fastest growing technology companies was well recognized through achievements that have garnered numerous awards including Canada’s Top 40 Under 40, Alberta’s Most Influential Top 50 People, Ernst and Young’s Entrepreneur of the Year, and the Certificate of Merit for Business Excellence by Industry, Science, and Technology Canada.





Greg Rude
Director of Corporate Sales





Greg Rude
Director of Corporate Sales





Greg Rude has over 20 years of experience selling industrial safety products and services into the North American marketplace. Greg was the North American Business Development Manager at BW Technologies before becoming the Western Zone Manager. Following the acquisition of BW Technologies by Honeywell, Greg took on the role of National Sales Manager at Honeywell Analytics.





Clark Swanson
Director, Business Development, Americas





Clark Swanson
Director, Business Development, Americas





Clark Swanson, previously held an executive position for SourceCode Technology Holdings, Inc., a global software firm headquartered in Redmond, Washington. Mr. Swanson has also served as Executive Vice President of Universal Studios based, White Eagle Productions, and Director of Immedient Corporation, a software services company headquartered in Mountain View, California. Mr. Swanson holds a degree in Economics from Pepperdine University and also graduated honors from the Graziadio School of Business & Management with an MBA, emphasis in Finance.





Bernadette Geronazzo
Director of Public & Investor Relations





Bernadette Geronazzo
Director of Public & Investor Relations





Bernadette Geronazzo is an Accredited Business Communicator with more than 15 years of experience in corporate communication plans, advertising and raising awareness for corporations with targeted audiences. She has worked with clients that range from independent business owners to multi-national corporations in the areas of public and investor relations, marketing, strategic planning as well as non-profit and community relations. She has co-directed and written for television, has been a columnist for the Calgary Herald as well as the Calgary Real Estate Board, and has worked in the role of Executive Director for a Business Revitalization Zone in Calgary.





Brendon Cook
Chief Technology Officer & Co-founder





Brendon Cook
Chief Technology Officer & Co-founder





Brendon Cook was awarded a B.Sc. in Geomatics Engineering from the University of Calgary. Prior to founding BlackLine GPS Inc. in 2004, Mr. Cook worked for Calgary-based CSI Wireless Inc. (now Hemisphere GPS Inc.) as its Product and Marketing Manager and developed business relationships with various international organizations. At CSI Wireless Inc., Mr. Cook managed the company’s precision product portfolio and was responsible for the market analysis, generating market analysis, generating market direction, defining new products, and assisted with managing the company’s product development program.










